WEBVTT

00:14.318 --> 00:17.321
Okay, I'm gonna ask you
a series of questions,

00:17.365 --> 00:20.368
and there are no right
or wrong answers.

00:22.326 --> 00:24.633
So when you think
about the future,

00:24.676 --> 00:26.852
how do you imagine it'll be?

00:28.028 --> 00:29.464
Like, what will
nature be like?

00:31.944 --> 00:33.250
How will your city change?

00:35.861 --> 00:37.254
Will families be the same?

00:40.562 --> 00:43.739
What will stay with you,
and what will you forget?

00:46.742 --> 00:47.786
What scares you?

00:47.830 --> 00:49.614
What makes you angry?

00:49.658 --> 00:50.920
Do you feel lonely?

00:51.790 --> 00:54.706
What makes you happy?

00:56.012 --> 00:57.666
[LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING]

01:00.060 --> 01:01.191
[SIREN BLARING DISTANTLY]

01:03.106 --> 01:04.934
So we are goin'
around the country,

01:04.977 --> 01:08.111
goin' to different cities
and interviewing kids,

01:08.155 --> 01:11.288
ranging in age, um, just
about their... their life

01:11.332 --> 01:14.117
and what they think
about the future.

01:14.161 --> 01:17.207
If I ask you anything
that you don't wanna answer,

01:17.251 --> 01:18.687
or you don't like a
question or whatever,

01:18.730 --> 01:20.341
you can just be like, "No."

01:20.384 --> 01:21.733
- I want you to just
feel comfortable,

01:21.777 --> 01:23.735
and if there's anything
that I ask you about

01:23.779 --> 01:25.041
that you don't
wanna talk about,

01:25.085 --> 01:26.608
say "I don't really
wanna talk about that."

01:26.651 --> 01:29.567
- I think adults always
think they're the boss,

01:29.611 --> 01:31.961
and they always gotta be
the boss of everything.

01:32.004 --> 01:34.268
And I think that some
adults have that mindset

01:34.311 --> 01:35.747
where "I'm right
and you're wrong."

01:35.791 --> 01:37.488
- When you think
about the future,

01:37.532 --> 01:39.186
how do you imagine it'll be?

01:40.056 --> 01:41.188
- I... [SIGHS]

01:41.231 --> 01:44.278
I imagine and hope
it'll be good.

01:46.149 --> 01:47.368
And do you ever think,

01:47.411 --> 01:48.978
like, what could
adults have done

01:49.021 --> 01:52.155
to have made sure that we
went in the right path?

01:52.199 --> 01:54.114
- Definitely most of all,
pay more attention

01:54.157 --> 01:56.203
to, like, what's
going on around them,

01:56.246 --> 01:58.161
'cause I feel like
that's a big problem

01:58.205 --> 02:00.424
with, like,
literally everything.

02:00.468 --> 02:02.339
Like, that's a big, big thing.

02:04.124 --> 02:05.299
They'll be like,
"Oh, you're from Detroit."

02:05.342 --> 02:06.430
I was like, "Yeah."

02:06.474 --> 02:07.736
Like, "It's really
dangerous there.

02:07.779 --> 02:09.564
The schools are
really terrible

02:09.607 --> 02:11.653
and, like, nothing's
good there."

02:11.696 --> 02:13.176
I was like, "Well,
how would you know?

02:13.220 --> 02:14.221
You don't live there,

02:14.264 --> 02:15.309
and you don't go
to school there.

02:15.352 --> 02:16.788
You weren't
raised in Detroit."

02:16.832 --> 02:19.791
Like, "I've been raised
in Detroit all my life."

02:19.835 --> 02:21.924
America,
uh, it's so much...

02:21.967 --> 02:23.578
It's so much tragedy,

02:23.621 --> 02:25.580
and some people
aren't treated fairly,

02:25.623 --> 02:28.278
because of race, because
of who they like,

02:28.322 --> 02:30.150
because of where they live,

02:30.193 --> 02:32.021
because of how much
money they have.

02:32.064 --> 02:34.241
So I would want it to
become a better place

02:34.284 --> 02:35.546
and people to know

02:35.590 --> 02:36.678
that just because
someone isn't like you

02:36.721 --> 02:38.245
doesn't mean that
they're wrong,

02:38.288 --> 02:39.855
but then I'm not sure.

02:39.898 --> 02:41.161
We're at
the point right now

02:41.204 --> 02:43.511
where we have to
change things,

02:43.554 --> 02:46.557
and just based on
our morals as people,

02:46.601 --> 02:48.907
I don't really see that
happening anytime soon.

02:51.171 --> 02:53.477
So, you're... You're
hopeful for the future?

02:53.521 --> 02:54.652
Like, when you think
about the future,

02:54.696 --> 02:57.264
you think it'll be
better or worse?

02:57.307 --> 02:58.569
For me,
personally,

02:58.613 --> 03:00.528
I feel like things
are gonna get better,

03:00.571 --> 03:04.053
because I have a lot of
opportunities right now.

03:04.096 --> 03:05.359
[OVER TAPE] I'm
hopeful for myself,

03:05.402 --> 03:06.882
for other people.

03:06.925 --> 03:08.971
I don't know if things
are gonna get better,

03:09.014 --> 03:10.190
it's really on the side,

03:10.233 --> 03:11.495
but I really hope
things get better.

03:12.496 --> 03:15.934
Um, but for the overall world,

03:17.197 --> 03:18.633
