responsibilities in your life,

55:02.124 --> 55:05.214
and sometimes they
just come to you,

55:05.258 --> 55:07.695
and you can't really
do anything about them.

55:07.739 --> 55:09.262
They're just there.

55:09.306 --> 55:10.785
I feel like a responsibility

55:10.829 --> 55:12.831
to like that I'm
proud to take,

55:12.874 --> 55:16.095
because I love her a lot,

55:16.138 --> 55:17.836
and basically, it
wouldn't matter to me

55:17.879 --> 55:20.317
if she sees me as a
father or a brother.

55:22.231 --> 55:25.191
Yeah, that's pretty
much it. [CHUCKLES]

55:25.234 --> 55:26.801
- You're a good man.

55:28.586 --> 55:31.545
How... How often do you...
do you get to visit your dad?

55:31.589 --> 55:33.068
[OVER TAPE] Always.

55:33.112 --> 55:35.941
Yeah, I feel like that's
one of my like motivations

55:35.984 --> 55:37.290
to just think
about the future.

55:37.334 --> 55:38.900
Everything that could happen...

55:38.944 --> 55:42.948
I ask for trust,
cooperation, and permission

55:42.991 --> 55:44.253
without knowing
where the experience

55:44.297 --> 55:46.212
will lead the subject.

55:46.255 --> 55:50.869
I can and will leave a place,
a situation, a problem,

55:50.912 --> 55:53.262
but the people I
interview cannot.

55:54.612 --> 55:55.917
The work offers
the interviewer

55:55.961 --> 55:57.789
access and a reason

55:57.832 --> 56:00.357
to stay in a world
that's not my own,

56:00.400 --> 56:03.316
complete distraction
from my own life,

56:03.360 --> 56:07.102
a sense of invincibility,
a sense of invisibility.

56:08.495 --> 56:11.150
I traffic in hope without
the ability to know

56:11.193 --> 56:12.586
what will happen
in the future.

56:14.283 --> 56:16.503
The work offers the
subjects a chance to speak

56:16.547 --> 56:18.810
of things they have
never spoken of,

56:18.853 --> 56:21.465
a chance to see
themselves as subjects

56:21.508 --> 56:23.510
worthy of time and attention.

56:25.164 --> 56:27.427
The work offers the subjects

56:27.471 --> 56:30.212
the creation of
an image of self,

56:30.256 --> 56:33.477
the distribution of
which they cannot control

56:33.520 --> 56:37.045
on a global scale,
in perpetuity.

56:38.699 --> 56:39.613
- ...you know, there's, like,

56:39.657 --> 56:40.788
a lot of Chinese
people actually,

56:40.832 --> 56:42.660
so it's not, like,
hard to communicate.

56:42.703 --> 56:45.140
Sometimes in other
places, I'm actually...

56:45.184 --> 56:46.968
[CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY]

